Diwali Sales Analysis¶

1.The focus of this project lies in conducting an in-depth analysis of Diwali sales.
2.The dataset under scrutiny comprises a total of 11,251 rows and 15 columns.
3.Leveraging tools such as pandas, numpy, and data visualization techniques, this analysis aims to uncover meaningful insights through exploratory data analysis.
4.The ultimate goal is to draw informed conclusions based on the comprehensive examination of the Diwali sales data.

Data Visulization¶

In [18]:
#Gender:
#1.Count of gender:
gender_count=sns.countplot(x='Gender',data=df)

for i in gender_count.containers:
    gender_count.bar_label(i)

Count of gender is more females shopping the product when compared to males.

In [19]:
#2.Which gender is more order the product/items:
gender1=df.groupby(['Gender'],as_index=False)['Orders'].sum().sort_values(by='Orders',ascending=False)

gender1_count=sns.barplot(x='Gender',y='Orders',data=gender1)

for i in gender1_count.containers:
    gender1_count.bar_label(i)

Females is more orders the product when compared to males.

In [17]:
#3.Which gender is more spending the money:
sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(5,5)})
gender3=df.groupby(['Gender'],as_index=False)['Amount'].sum().sort_values(by='Amount',ascending=False)

gender3_count=sns.barplot(x='Gender',y='Amount',data=gender3)

Females is more amount the product when compared to males.

Conclusion¶

In summary, the predominant demographic displaying heightened interest in pursuing the specified analysis data comprises unmarried females within the age range of 26 to 35. This trend is particularly pronounced among residents of Uttar Pradesh, specifically those employed in the IT sector. Notably, individuals situated in the central zone exhibit a notable inclination towards pursuing the identified patterns and preferences.
